
1. Analyse the economic benefits of Genetically Modified crops and public opinion in the United States
We aim to explore the correlation between GM corn and Agricultural GDP by state, as well as public opinion and GM crops.

2. Address misinformation regarding GM crops
As a very controvercial topic, we aim to dissuade common myths regarding GM crops and present the current state of agriculture and GM crops using data and maps.
 
3. Create a base for future exploration in other countries 
Genetically modified crops have potential for economic growth and can address many other issues, especially in developing countries. We hope that our findings raise awareness and are a starting point for future research and debate. 
